Pero Adeniyi, first baby mama to Nigerian singer, Innocent Idibia popularly known as Tuface, has reacted as his wife, Annie Macaulay-Idibia lamented over giving birth to his fifth child despite being the first love. Annie disclosed this in in a Netflix TV show, titled Young, Rich and African, expressing how she felt when Tuface had children from other women while expressing when they were still dating. She said, “When you meet someone and then you know them first, but when you wake up, two different people are having a baby for him. “He has five kids with other women. My first child is his fifth, and I met him before everybody. So you know what that is. Do you know how much humiliation and embarrassment (I faced)?” In a recent video post by Pero via her Instagram page, showing her three children which she had for Tuface, she wrote, “perosaiyemi_ Me i get Sense I get GOD, I come 1st, I don boss, Plenty talk , Plenty noise, Aye ole f’eni t’omo way Eni t’omo way, sheb’oun l’omo Barnabas? Oshe kizz bobo! “Incredible! Unbeatable! Palatable! Unshakable , Unsinkable Gudugudu akinkanju arakangudu Obirin mewa! — #billiondollarbaby #iyaawonomoolorire.” Recall that Tuface has seven children by three women, including his wife, Annie who has two daughters for him. His second baby mama, Sumbo Adeoye, who is now married to Pastor David Adeoye has two boys for him, while Pero has three kids comprising two boys and a girl for the Nigerian singer.